# AAI (Autonomous Agent Interface)

This project uses AAI for structured Planning → Implementation → Validation workflows.

## Always do this first
Read `.aai/AGENTS.md` before starting any development work.

## Skill invocation in Cursor
Skills are prompt files. Invoke by reading and following the file:
- New work: read `.aai/SKILL_INTAKE.prompt.md`
- Full autonomous loop: read `.aai/SKILL_LOOP.prompt.md`
- Check state: read `.aai/SKILL_CHECK_STATE.prompt.md`
- TDD cycle: read `.aai/SKILL_TDD.prompt.md`
- Code review: read `.aai/SKILL_CODE_REVIEW.prompt.md`
- All skills: see `.aai/AGENTS.md` → Skills section

## Core rules
- Requirements → Spec → Implementation → Evidence (traceability required)
- Never claim completion without running tests and checking exit codes
- Do not invent frameworks — read `docs/TECHNOLOGY.md` first
- If STATE.yaml exists, read it before any role dispatch

## Workflow
1. `/aai-intake` (or read SKILL_INTAKE.prompt.md) — register new work
2. Orchestration dispatches Planning → Implementation → Validation automatically
3. `/aai-loop` runs the full cycle autonomously
4. `/aai-hitl` unblocks when human input is required
